g.text: The land required to do that could use up to 1.2 billion hectares. To put this number in perspective: current global cropland uses about 1.5 billion hectares. In other words, BECCS would require 80% of the amount we already use to grow food.
Most scenarios aim to a much higher level; the median of the 1.5° scenarios commits to using BECCS to capture 12 gigatons of CO2, or the amount being emitted in 1967.
